## Styling Requirements

### Button Styling
- Start game buttons: `className="w-full bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700"`
- Back buttons: `variant="outline" size="sm"`
- Action buttons: Use appropriate semantic variants

### Card Styling
- Game setup cards: Standard card with header/content
- Success cards: `className="border-green-200 bg-green-50"`
- Hover effects: `className="cursor-pointer transition-colors hover:bg-muted/50"`

### Icon Usage
- Hangman: `Target` icon
- Crossword: `Grid3x3` icon
- General: `BookOpen`, `Trophy`, `ArrowLeft` as appropriate

### Color Scheme
- Primary: Blue theme (`text-blue-600`, `bg-blue-50`)
- Success: Green theme (`text-green-700`, `bg-green-50`)
- Purple: Action buttons (`bg-purple-600`)
- Difficulty badges: Green (easy), Blue (medium), Purple (hard)

## Game Logic Patterns

### State Management
```typescript
// Use useCallback for game functions
const makeGuess = useCallback((input: string) => {
  if (gameState.gameStatus !== 'playing') return
  // Game logic
}, [gameState])

// Use useEffect for initialization
useEffect(() => {
  if (vocabularyTerms.length > 0) {
    initializeGame()
  }
}, [vocabularyTerms, difficulty])
```

### Hint System Implementation
```typescript
const useHint = useCallback(() => {
  if (gameState.hintsUsed >= maxHints) return
  
  setGameState(prev => ({
    ...prev,
    hintsUsed: prev.hintsUsed + 1,
    score: Math.max(0, prev.score - 5) // Deduct points
  }))
  
  setShowHint(true)
}, [gameState.hintsUsed, maxHints])
```

### Game Completion
```typescript
const completeGame = useCallback(() => {
  const timeSpent = Math.floor((Date.now() - gameState.startTime) / 1000)
  
  setGameState(prev => ({
    ...prev,
    gameStatus: 'won' // or 'lost'
  }))
  
  onGameComplete?.(gameState.score, totalWords, timeSpent)
}, [gameState, onGameComplete])
```

## Data Handling

### Vocabulary Context Usage
```typescript
const { vocabularySets, loading, error } = useVocabulary()

// Filter terms by difficulty
const availableTerms = selectedSet?.terms.filter(term => 
  !difficulty || term.difficulty === difficulty || !term.difficulty
) || []
```

### Term Selection
```typescript
// Shuffle and limit terms for game
const gameTerms = useMemo(() => {
  const shuffled = [...availableTerms].sort(() => Math.random() - 0.5)
  return shuffled.slice(0, Math.min(10, shuffled.length))
}, [availableTerms])
```

## Responsive Design

### Grid Layouts
- Two-column: `className="grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-2"`
- Three-column: `className="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3"`
- Single column on mobile: Always stack vertically

### Interactive Elements
- Ensure touch-friendly sizing (minimum 44px touch targets)
- Use appropriate hover states for desktop
- Handle keyboard navigation for accessibility

## Error Handling

### Loading States
```typescript
if (loading) {
  return (
    <div className="container mx-auto px-4 py-8">
      <div className="flex items-center justify-center min-h-[400px]">
        <div className="animate-spin rounded-full h-8 w-8 border-b-2 border-primary"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  )
}
```

### Empty States
```typescript
if (vocabularySets.length === 0) {
  return (
    <div className="text-center py-8">
      <p className="text-muted-foreground">No vocabulary sets available</p>
      <Button asChild className="mt-4">
        <Link href="/admin/vocabulary">Create Vocabulary Set</Link>
      </Button>
    </div>
  )
}
```

### Game Validation
- Always validate vocabulary set selection before starting
- Check for minimum number of terms
- Handle edge cases gracefully